snippet: The Trust for Public Land looked at factors including park access, size, services and public investment.
abstract: Trust for Public Land ranks New York City’s park system second, behind Minneapolis’s, in  survey of nation’s 50 largest cities; success of New York City is an affirmation of tenure of Adrian Benepe, who served as New York City parks commissioner for more than a decade.
lead_paragraph: The Trust for Public Land looked at factors including park access, size, services and public investment.

headline.seo: New York City’s Park System Ranked No. 2 in Survey of 50 Cities
headline.main: New York Parks Rank No. 2 in a Survey of 50 U.S. Cities
